  "body": "/kind feature\r\n/sig node\r\n\r\n*Scenario*\r\n\r\nUpdateNodeStatus operation requires Read / Write operations to the api-server, these activities are used to provide an updated vision of the node to the controller-manager.\r\n\r\nWhen the node manages multiple volumes, there is an additional number of request that kubelet trigger to the API manager. By default, kubelet request is under a flow control, which implements a rate limit. \r\n\r\nThis rate limit block the update operation causing the controller to flip the node status and ultimately evict healthy pods.\r\n\r\n\r\n*Expectation*\r\n\r\nIndependent of the flow control management configuration, the node heartbeat (UpdateNodeStatus),  should not honour the rate request. We expect that kubelet to report the node status as fast as possible independent of the node load or status.\r\n\r\n*Additional considerations*\r\n\r\nA slow node update is affected by other process modifying the node status, like the node problem detector. In this case, it is normal to have conflicts in the update request.\r\n",
